1
00:00:18,148 --> 00:00:20,582
<i>[ Owl Hooting ]</i>

2
00:00:22,052 --> 00:00:24,486
<i>[ Wolf Howling ]</i>

3
00:00:38,569 --> 00:00:40,833
[ Groans ]

4
00:00:47,044 --> 00:00:49,638
<i>[ Bird Squawking ]</i>

5
00:01:14,838 --> 00:01:19,366
[ Boots Rattling ]

6
00:01:33,824 --> 00:01:37,021
[ Rattling Continues ]

7
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:46,331
[ Gurgling ]

8
00:02:03,687 --> 00:02:06,781
<i>[ Wolf Howling ]</i>

9
00:02:12,930 --> 00:02:18,766
<i>[ Man's Voice ]
l am the lord of darkness.</i>

10
00:02:18,835 --> 00:02:24,501
<i>l require the solace
of the shadows...</i>

11
00:02:24,575 --> 00:02:28,534
<i>and the dark of the night.</i>

12
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:34,913
<i>Sunshine is my destroyer.</i>

13
00:02:37,221 --> 00:02:40,554
<i>All this shall change.</i>

14
00:02:42,559 --> 00:02:47,223
<i>Tonight, the sun sets forever.</i>

15
00:02:49,132 --> 00:02:53,466
<i>There shall never be
another dawn...</i>

16
00:02:53,537 --> 00:02:57,405
<i>[ Knocking ]
Enter!</i>

17
00:02:57,474 --> 00:03:02,878
<i>[ Door Creaking ]</i>

18
00:03:02,946 --> 00:03:06,006
<i>[ Boots Rattling ]</i>

19
00:03:08,752 --> 00:03:11,687
<i>Ah, Blix.</i>

20
00:03:11,755 --> 00:03:14,622
Come closer.

21
00:03:17,728 --> 00:03:20,322
<i>You summoned me, lordship?</i>

22
00:03:21,999 --> 00:03:25,560
Are you not the most loathsome
of my goblins?

23
00:03:25,636 --> 00:03:29,367
[ Gurgling ]
Truly, master.

24
00:03:29,439 --> 00:03:34,001
And is your heart black
and full of hate?

25
00:03:34,077 --> 00:03:37,205
Black as midnight,
black as pitch,

26
00:03:37,281 --> 00:03:39,511
blacker than
the foulest witch.

27
00:03:39,583 --> 00:03:42,279
That is why
I have called you here.

28
00:03:42,352 --> 00:03:46,982
Since I must remain in darkness,
you shall be my eyes and ears.

29
00:03:47,057 --> 00:03:49,958
You do me
great honor, lord.

30
00:03:52,529 --> 00:03:55,430
<i>Something troubles me.</i>

31
00:03:55,499 --> 00:03:58,400
<i>l feel a presence
in the forest,</i>

32
00:03:59,936 --> 00:04:03,497
<i>a force l had mercifully
almost forgotten.</i>

33
00:04:03,573 --> 00:04:06,940
Must be dread, indeed,
to trouble you, lordship.

34
00:04:07,010 --> 00:04:09,945
Looking upon
these frail creatures,

35
00:04:10,013 --> 00:04:13,505
one would not think that
they could contain such power.

36
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:17,280
One could rule
the universe with it.

37
00:04:17,354 --> 00:04:22,553
You must find them for me
and destroy them!

38
00:04:22,626 --> 00:04:27,427
[ Gurgling ]
What do they look like, lord?

39
00:04:27,497 --> 00:04:31,957
Fool! Let this
serve to remind you.

40
00:04:32,035 --> 00:04:35,095
They are each crowned
with a single horn...

41
00:04:35,172 --> 00:04:37,800
reaching straight
to heaven.

42
00:04:37,874 --> 00:04:40,502
I get the point, lord.

43
00:04:40,577 --> 00:04:43,478
Bring the horns to me.

44
00:04:43,547 --> 00:04:45,674
<i>You will be well rewarded.</i>

45
00:04:45,749 --> 00:04:49,241
<i>You shall be a prince
here in my realm.</i>

46
00:04:49,319 --> 00:04:52,152
A rare privilege, master.

47
00:04:54,725 --> 00:04:57,660
[ Sighs ]
Where shall I look, sire?

48
00:04:57,728 --> 00:05:02,597
There is only one lure
for such disgusting goodness,

49
00:05:02,666 --> 00:05:05,931
one bait that never fails.

50
00:05:06,002 --> 00:05:09,494
What be this bait?
Please, you teach me.

51
00:05:09,573 --> 00:05:13,600
Innocence. Innocence.

52
00:05:15,512 --> 00:05:17,878
[ Woman Humming ]

53
00:05:42,539 --> 00:05:45,770
Come, white flowers

54
00:05:45,842 --> 00:05:48,640
Weave us a carpet

55
00:05:48,712 --> 00:05:50,839
Spreading oak

56
00:05:50,914 --> 00:05:54,077
Make a shade where we lie

57
00:05:54,151 --> 00:05:59,316
Leaves and branches
whisper our love song

58
00:05:59,389 --> 00:06:04,759
When I look
in my true love's eyes

59
00:06:04,828 --> 00:06:09,765
Young as any spring

60
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:14,497
His eyes almost sing

61
00:06:14,571 --> 00:06:18,200
<i>To me</i>

62
00:06:18,275 --> 00:06:21,244
[ Humming Continues ]

63
00:06:23,313 --> 00:06:26,146
<i>[ Rooster Crows ]</i>

64
00:06:37,794 --> 00:06:42,356
[ Gurgling ]

65
00:06:51,975 --> 00:06:56,036
[ Humming ]

66
00:07:00,050 --> 00:07:02,143
Blooming fairies!

67
00:07:05,822 --> 00:07:08,416
[ Snoring ]

68
00:07:12,229 --> 00:07:14,925
<i>[ Birds Fluttering ]</i>

69
00:07:24,574 --> 00:07:27,475
[ Birds Chirping ]

70
00:07:41,291 --> 00:07:44,385
<i>[ Clock Clattering ]</i>

71
00:07:51,167 --> 00:07:55,797
[ Clock Chiming ]

72
00:08:10,420 --> 00:08:13,150
<i>[ Woman ]
Lily!</i>

73
00:08:13,223 --> 00:08:16,283
<i>God bless, Your Highness.</i>

74
00:08:16,359 --> 00:08:19,089
A royal visit's
always a pleasure.

75
00:08:19,162 --> 00:08:21,392
Have another biscuit.

76
00:08:28,905 --> 00:08:31,373
Nell...

77
00:08:33,243 --> 00:08:35,507
I have no time to stay
for a visit today.

78
00:08:35,579 --> 00:08:37,570
Oh, you've got
a sweetheart waiting?

79
00:08:37,647 --> 00:08:42,277
No, I don't.
Surely, your father
forbids such folly.

80
00:08:42,352 --> 00:08:45,287
What my father doesn't know
won't trouble him.

81
00:08:45,355 --> 00:08:48,449
Oh, the willful heart
invites despair,

82
00:08:48,525 --> 00:08:51,323
like blind men creeping
in a dragon's lair.

83
00:08:51,394 --> 00:08:53,760
Not a country proverb
nor king's command...

84
00:08:53,830 --> 00:08:55,195
<i>could keep me
from the woods today.</i>

85
00:08:55,265 --> 00:09:01,602
Then it's common sense sort.
Lily. Princess Lily.

86
00:09:01,671 --> 00:09:06,335
I look on you as a daughter.
If you'll pardon my saying it,

87
00:09:06,409 --> 00:09:10,175
it's time you started behaving
like the princess you are.

88
00:09:10,246 --> 00:09:13,943
<i>You should be out looking
for a handsome prince
on a white charger,</i>

89
00:09:14,017 --> 00:09:16,713
not visiting
poor folk like us.

90
00:09:16,786 --> 00:09:21,917
No. Don't you know
I love coming here?

91
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:26,720
[ Sighs ]

92
00:09:26,796 --> 00:09:29,629
This place holds
more magic for me...

93
00:09:29,699 --> 00:09:31,963
than any palace
in the world.

94
00:09:32,035 --> 00:09:35,562
You live a very rich
life, Nell.

95
00:09:35,639 --> 00:09:37,971
I don't know of a prince
who could carve wood like this.

96
00:09:38,041 --> 00:09:40,737
You're very sweet, Lily.

97
00:09:43,513 --> 00:09:46,949
Magic is a wonderful thing.

98
00:09:47,017 --> 00:09:49,952
<i>You'll find your own magic
one day.</i>

99
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:52,284
<i>l'm sure you will.</i>

100
00:09:53,657 --> 00:09:56,922
I have no time for this.
I'm going.

101
00:10:01,197 --> 00:10:03,961
Oh, and you look out
for spriggen and banshee,
my girl.

102
00:10:04,034 --> 00:10:06,093
These woods
be thick with them.

103
00:10:06,169 --> 00:10:10,162
Stay clear of toadstool
rings and willow trees...

104
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:12,504
<i>and old oaks.</i>

105
00:10:12,575 --> 00:10:14,509
[ Lily ]
Jack!

106
00:10:16,713 --> 00:10:18,408
Where are you?

107
00:10:22,318 --> 00:10:24,252
Jack!

108
00:10:32,996 --> 00:10:36,488
- [ Gurgling ]
-Jack! Jack!

109
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:47,032
Jack?

110
00:10:56,519 --> 00:10:58,453
Jack?

111
00:11:00,090 --> 00:11:02,217
Jack, answer me.

112
00:11:02,292 --> 00:11:04,852
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

113
00:11:09,466 --> 00:11:12,128
<i>[ Goblin Croaks ]</i>

114
00:11:15,872 --> 00:11:18,739
Jack! Jack!

115
00:11:18,808 --> 00:11:20,742
<i>[ Voice Echoing ]
Jack.</i>

116
00:11:20,810 --> 00:11:25,645
Jack, please.
Please, if you're here,
say something to me, please.

117
00:11:26,983 --> 00:11:29,884
[ Screams ]

118
00:11:31,221 --> 00:11:35,157
Jack, you scared
the life out of me!
[ Laughing ]

119
00:11:35,225 --> 00:11:38,058
[ Whistling, Chirping ]

120
00:11:46,503 --> 00:11:48,130
You're so clever.

121
00:11:50,039 --> 00:11:52,200
Oh, here.

122
00:11:52,275 --> 00:11:55,540
<i>Whoops. Look inside.
See what you can find.</i>

123
00:12:00,316 --> 00:12:02,841
That's something to eat.

124
00:12:04,754 --> 00:12:07,279
<i>[ Laughs ]
l made that for you myself.</i>

125
00:12:12,495 --> 00:12:16,659
Well, I-I took it from Nell.

126
00:12:16,733 --> 00:12:20,897
<i>[ Laughs ]
Do you like it? ls it sweet?</i>

127
00:12:26,309 --> 00:12:29,176
I know someone sweeter.

128
00:12:29,245 --> 00:12:31,941
May be innocent,
may be sweet...

129
00:12:32,015 --> 00:12:36,281
<i>ain't half as nice
as rotting meat.</i>

130
00:12:36,352 --> 00:12:39,082
[ Snorting ]

131
00:12:42,659 --> 00:12:45,651
[ Whistling ]

132
00:12:52,402 --> 00:12:56,839
Good. Very good.
Just right.

133
00:12:58,174 --> 00:13:01,769
Jack, now teach me rabbit
like you promised.

134
00:13:01,845 --> 00:13:03,779
Rabbit?

135
00:13:05,682 --> 00:13:08,515
It's much harder
than finch.
Let me try.

136
00:13:08,585 --> 00:13:12,817
I'm a good student,
and my father says
I'm brilliant.

137
00:13:14,657 --> 00:13:17,490
[ Jingling ]
See how brilliant I am?

138
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:20,358
Let me dazzle you
with my wisdom.

139
00:13:20,430 --> 00:13:23,831
It's much more than wisdom
that dazzles me, Lily.

140
00:13:26,870 --> 00:13:28,804
Jack, teach me rabbit.

141
00:13:28,872 --> 00:13:30,965
Not today.

142
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,974
Why not?

143
00:13:33,042 --> 00:13:35,306
Because...

144
00:13:38,548 --> 00:13:42,416
there's something
really special that I've
been promising to show you.

145
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:47,180
-Jack, do you mean it?
- Only if it pleases you, Lily.

146
00:13:47,257 --> 00:13:50,420
Oh, it pleases me
more than anything.

147
00:13:50,493 --> 00:13:52,825
We must go now...

148
00:13:52,896 --> 00:13:56,024
because they'll only be here
for a short while.

149
00:14:00,470 --> 00:14:02,768
Don't you trust me?

150
00:14:05,842 --> 00:14:08,367
I trust you, Lily.

151
00:15:43,740 --> 00:15:46,607
Oh, Jack.
[ Laughs ]

152
00:16:20,743 --> 00:16:23,576
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

153
00:17:14,363 --> 00:17:17,890
<i>Look! Ugly
one-horned mules.</i>

154
00:17:28,611 --> 00:17:30,704
Nothing is more magical.

155
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:32,714
[ Whinnying ]

156
00:17:32,782 --> 00:17:35,774
<i>As long as they roam
the earth,</i>

157
00:17:35,852 --> 00:17:38,719
evil can never harm
the pure of heart.

158
00:17:54,036 --> 00:17:56,004
Do you speak
their language?

159
00:17:57,607 --> 00:18:00,838
<i>They express
only love and laughter.</i>

160
00:18:00,910 --> 00:18:03,344
Dark thoughts
are unknown to them.

161
00:18:06,482 --> 00:18:09,747
No! No.

162
00:18:18,161 --> 00:18:20,356
Please.

163
00:18:44,687 --> 00:18:47,349
Lily, no, please!

164
00:19:09,145 --> 00:19:12,137
Come dance, sparrow

165
00:19:12,215 --> 00:19:14,740
Sing me good morning

166
00:19:14,817 --> 00:19:16,944
Rise up, sun

167
00:19:17,019 --> 00:19:19,613
<i>Like the arch of the sky</i>

168
00:19:22,758 --> 00:19:25,659
[ Whinnying ]

169
00:19:25,728 --> 00:19:29,687
<i>[ Rumbling ]</i>

170
00:19:29,765 --> 00:19:34,065
<i>- [ Growling ]
- [ Horses Neighing ]</i>

171
00:19:34,136 --> 00:19:36,434
[ Neighing Continues ]

172
00:19:59,495 --> 00:20:02,896
<i>[ Neighing Continues ]</i>

173
00:20:23,452 --> 00:20:27,286
You'll spook the beast
and spoil the trap.

174
00:20:36,532 --> 00:20:39,399
<i>[ Unicorn Whinnies ]</i>

175
00:20:53,416 --> 00:20:56,146
Living river

176
00:20:56,218 --> 00:20:59,676
Turn the light to diamonds

177
00:20:59,755 --> 00:21:04,454
<i>When l look
in my true love's eyes</i>

178
00:21:04,527 --> 00:21:07,860
Like a child feels

179
00:21:07,930 --> 00:21:10,490
Watching a rainbow

180
00:21:10,566 --> 00:21:12,796
<i>Like a bird feels</i>

181
00:21:12,868 --> 00:21:15,462
<i>The first time it flies</i>

182
00:21:15,538 --> 00:21:17,938
<i>l feel magic</i>

183
00:21:18,007 --> 00:21:20,771
Stirring within me

184
00:21:20,843 --> 00:21:25,712
<i>When l look
in my true love's eyes</i>

185
00:21:25,781 --> 00:21:30,718
Young as any spring

186
00:21:30,786 --> 00:21:35,587
His eyes almost seem

187
00:21:38,761 --> 00:21:41,889
This shot be
just as sweet as pie.

188
00:21:46,936 --> 00:21:49,336
[ Whinnies ]

189
00:21:55,978 --> 00:22:00,176
[ Squeals, Neighing ]

190
00:22:13,662 --> 00:22:17,257
Jack? Jack?

191
00:22:19,101 --> 00:22:21,035
Jack!

192
00:22:22,338 --> 00:22:25,307
It was lovely...
like a dream.

193
00:22:25,374 --> 00:22:27,740
<i>[ Jack ]
What you did is forbidden.</i>

194
00:22:27,810 --> 00:22:30,438
Who says so?

195
00:22:30,513 --> 00:22:34,244
<i>lt is known, Lily.
These are sacred animals.</i>

196
00:22:34,316 --> 00:22:38,548
<i>- l don't care.
- You risk your immortal soul
talking like that.</i>

197
00:22:42,792 --> 00:22:47,752
I only wanted to touch one.
Where's the harm in that?

198
00:22:51,167 --> 00:22:52,691
It was magic.

199
00:22:54,937 --> 00:22:57,064
Thank you.

200
00:22:58,874 --> 00:23:01,104
Let me sing to you.

201
00:23:02,678 --> 00:23:05,772
I'll chase your fears away.

202
00:23:05,848 --> 00:23:11,582
<i>ln the bumps and the hollows</i>

203
00:23:11,654 --> 00:23:16,591
<i>The sunlight and shadows</i>

204
00:23:16,659 --> 00:23:20,618
<i>He kissed her as those</i>

205
00:23:20,696 --> 00:23:24,723
<i>Bluebells blow</i>

206
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:30,204
<i>As his lips met her breath</i>

207
00:23:30,272 --> 00:23:35,073
<i>He went sweetly to death</i>

208
00:23:35,144 --> 00:23:39,308
<i>At the roots
of the bluebells</i>

209
00:23:39,381 --> 00:23:43,283
<i>ls where he is laid</i>

210
00:23:47,923 --> 00:23:50,949
[ Laughs ]
Are you afraid
to kiss me, Jack?

211
00:23:51,026 --> 00:23:53,358
I'm afraid
you'll break my heart.

212
00:23:53,429 --> 00:23:55,454
Then still your heart.

213
00:23:55,531 --> 00:23:58,466
You're dear to me
as life itself.

214
00:24:00,202 --> 00:24:02,329
Don't you wish this
was our wedding ring?

215
00:24:02,404 --> 00:24:04,338
If I say yes,
will my wish come true?

216
00:24:04,406 --> 00:24:06,738
I'm a princess.

217
00:24:06,809 --> 00:24:10,245
It's my right to set
a challenge for my suitors.

218
00:24:10,312 --> 00:24:13,679
[ Laughs ]
I will marry...

219
00:24:13,749 --> 00:24:15,842
whoever finds this ring.

220
00:24:20,890 --> 00:24:23,484
Jack!

221
00:24:44,847 --> 00:24:47,145
[ Screaming ]

222
00:24:50,085 --> 00:24:52,349
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

223
00:25:38,334 --> 00:25:43,101
[ Screaming Continues ]

224
00:25:52,081 --> 00:25:54,140
[ Neighing ]

225
00:26:11,634 --> 00:26:13,829
[ Thud ]

226
00:26:26,048 --> 00:26:28,073
[ Neighing ]

227
00:26:32,554 --> 00:26:35,250
[ Gasping ]

228
00:26:36,992 --> 00:26:39,426
[ Groaning ]

229
00:26:39,495 --> 00:26:43,022
[ Squealing ]

230
00:26:46,635 --> 00:26:50,867
Lily!

231
00:27:26,842 --> 00:27:29,276
[ Panting ]

232
00:27:49,965 --> 00:27:53,958
<i>[ Fiendish Cackling ]</i>

233
00:28:05,814 --> 00:28:09,250
I smell human flesh!

234
00:28:09,318 --> 00:28:12,446
[ Laughter Continues ]

235
00:28:12,521 --> 00:28:16,753
<i>[ Blix ]
After you, Pig.
Oh, no, after you.</i>

236
00:28:30,806 --> 00:28:33,604
[ Groaning ]

237
00:28:35,244 --> 00:28:38,702
<i>Clock. Mortal world
turned to ice.</i>

238
00:28:38,781 --> 00:28:42,683
Here be goblin paradise!
[ Laughing ]

239
00:28:42,751 --> 00:28:45,948
<i>Plenty hospitality here.</i>

240
00:28:46,021 --> 00:28:48,717
Baby!

241
00:28:48,791 --> 00:28:51,954
<i>l simply adore milk-fed meat.</i>

242
00:28:52,027 --> 00:28:54,325
<i>What are you,
some kind of animal?</i>

243
00:28:54,396 --> 00:28:57,729
<i>[ Gurgling, Groaning ]</i>

244
00:28:59,868 --> 00:29:02,666
<i>Ohh.</i>

245
00:29:04,139 --> 00:29:08,473
<i>- [ Squeals ]
- How did you do that, Blix?</i>

246
00:29:08,544 --> 00:29:10,705
Yeah, tell us how
you do those tricks.

247
00:29:10,779 --> 00:29:12,906
Quite easy, actually.

248
00:29:14,683 --> 00:29:17,743
- [ Gasps ]
- Goblin omelette.

249
00:29:17,820 --> 00:29:20,687
- Very nice, very nice.
- [ Squeals ]

250
00:29:20,756 --> 00:29:25,284
[ Laughing ]
Lucky day! Kill
ugly one-horned dead!

251
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:29,694
You act like you do all.
It was me who shoot
the poisoned stinger.

252
00:29:29,765 --> 00:29:32,427
Me! Me! Me!

253
00:29:32,501 --> 00:29:35,698
You only got the shot in
because the princess was there.

254
00:29:35,771 --> 00:29:38,604
Wrong! 'Twas beauty
led the beast to bay.

255
00:29:38,674 --> 00:29:43,771
<i>She was so sweet.
l could eat her brains like jam.</i>

256
00:29:43,846 --> 00:29:47,145
- I could suck her bones--
- Enough!

257
00:29:47,216 --> 00:29:51,550
Better hurry. Dark Lord,
he don't like to wait.

258
00:29:51,620 --> 00:29:55,147
- [ Snorting ]
- Mmmm.

259
00:29:55,224 --> 00:29:58,125
[ Yells, Laughing ]

260
00:30:00,863 --> 00:30:04,299
- [ Laughing Continues ]
- [ Gasps ]

261
00:30:07,336 --> 00:30:11,898
<i>[ Door Slams ]
[ Grunts, Sobbing ]</i>

262
00:30:11,974 --> 00:30:16,536
- Hyah! Hyah! Hyah!
- What have I done?

263
00:30:16,612 --> 00:30:18,546
[ Sobbing Continues ]

264
00:30:18,614 --> 00:30:22,243
<i>Four, five, six!
Hurray for Blix!</i>

265
00:30:22,317 --> 00:30:25,878
<i>[ Laughs ]
I'll make it right.</i>

266
00:30:35,297 --> 00:30:37,891
<i>[ Wolf Howling ]</i>

267
00:30:49,444 --> 00:30:52,880
[ Faint Humming ]

268
00:30:56,551 --> 00:30:58,485
[ Beam ]
Jack.

269
00:31:00,756 --> 00:31:02,883
[ Laughing ]

270
00:31:06,595 --> 00:31:09,223
Lily? Lily?

271
00:31:12,434 --> 00:31:15,460
-Jack?
- [ Gasps ]

272
00:31:16,872 --> 00:31:20,433
- [ Squeaking ]
- Who's there?

273
00:31:22,210 --> 00:31:24,201
<i>Who are you?</i>

274
00:31:24,279 --> 00:31:27,771
Here be forest child
and not know the Gump?

275
00:31:27,849 --> 00:31:31,046
<i>[ Fairies Giggling ]
Gump, is it?</i>

276
00:31:31,119 --> 00:31:34,577
Honeythorn Gump
at your service.

277
00:31:38,226 --> 00:31:40,285
[ Fairies Muttering ]

278
00:31:40,362 --> 00:31:43,263
[ Fairies Giggling ]

279
00:31:48,136 --> 00:31:50,764
I, I must be dreaming.

280
00:31:50,839 --> 00:31:55,776
If life is a dream,
better you dread the waking.

281
00:31:55,844 --> 00:31:59,575
Jack?
Stop it!

282
00:31:59,648 --> 00:32:02,139
<i>That's Oona.
She likes you.
Go away!</i>

283
00:32:02,217 --> 00:32:05,277
Does your blood
run so cold, Jack?

284
00:32:05,354 --> 00:32:08,846
You'll be a gobs
before your time.

285
00:32:08,924 --> 00:32:11,586
How'd you know my name?

286
00:32:13,762 --> 00:32:17,220
How does
a migrating swallow...

287
00:32:17,299 --> 00:32:20,393
know the way south
in winter?

288
00:32:20,469 --> 00:32:22,699
Or a spawning salmon...

289
00:32:22,771 --> 00:32:25,399
find the very source
of his birth...

290
00:32:25,474 --> 00:32:30,411
from the cold, black depth
of the mysterious sea?

291
00:32:30,479 --> 00:32:33,971
I know everything, Jack.

292
00:32:34,049 --> 00:32:36,313
Everything?

293
00:32:42,224 --> 00:32:46,092
Then why is it like this?
Why is there winter now?

294
00:32:48,897 --> 00:32:52,333
I'd be a powerful wizard,
indeed, could I answer.

295
00:32:52,401 --> 00:32:54,335
Suppose you tell me, Jack.

296
00:32:54,403 --> 00:32:56,337
Me?

297
00:32:57,906 --> 00:33:01,307
You know these woods
as well as any elf.

298
00:33:07,883 --> 00:33:11,614
Did you not see
something odd today?

299
00:33:11,686 --> 00:33:14,211
Any strange spirits?

300
00:33:14,289 --> 00:33:16,723
Did nothing untoward happen?

301
00:33:19,227 --> 00:33:21,161
No.

302
00:33:21,229 --> 00:33:27,065
No? No?
Nothing?

303
00:33:27,135 --> 00:33:31,003
Uh, I did take Lily
to see the Unicorns.

304
00:33:31,073 --> 00:33:34,668
- You did what?
- [ Murmuring ]

305
00:33:34,743 --> 00:33:37,678
Silence!

306
00:33:42,384 --> 00:33:44,352
Oh, God, Gump,
she touched him.

307
00:33:44,419 --> 00:33:48,287
Touched it? A mortal
laid hands on a Unicorn?

308
00:33:48,356 --> 00:33:52,224
<i>Jack! Squawk, squawk,
no more talk!</i>

309
00:33:54,563 --> 00:33:59,023
Do you think you can upset
the order of the universe
and not pay the price?

310
00:33:59,101 --> 00:34:02,093
[ Fairies Murmuring ]
But she meant no wrong!

311
00:34:06,942 --> 00:34:09,706
<i>[ Jack ]
What l did is done,
but l did it for love.</i>

312
00:34:09,778 --> 00:34:13,145
- [ Snickering ]
- Silence!

313
00:34:14,516 --> 00:34:19,476
Love, you say?
But answer me this riddle,

314
00:34:19,554 --> 00:34:21,647
and all will be forgiven.

315
00:34:22,757 --> 00:34:25,123
<i>And if l cannot?
Why, Jack,</i>

316
00:34:25,193 --> 00:34:28,253
then 'tis your death song
I'll be playing.

317
00:34:28,330 --> 00:34:31,959
[ Giggling, Murmuring ]

318
00:34:32,033 --> 00:34:34,501
Then ask away...

319
00:34:34,569 --> 00:34:37,595
<i>and pray God
my answer pleases you.</i>

320
00:34:57,225 --> 00:34:59,887
What is a bell
that does not ring...

321
00:34:59,961 --> 00:35:02,930
yet its knell
makes the angels sing?

322
00:35:02,998 --> 00:35:06,593
<i>- [ Fairies Murmuring ]
- Shhh!</i>

323
00:35:08,670 --> 00:35:11,537
Answer me this...

324
00:35:11,606 --> 00:35:14,404
<i>and all will be forgiven.</i>

325
00:35:18,046 --> 00:35:20,674
[ Quiet Murmuring ]

326
00:35:31,426 --> 00:35:34,395
- Flowers?
- [ Gasps ]

327
00:35:34,462 --> 00:35:38,023
Bluebells! To hear them ring
means your life is at an end!

328
00:35:38,099 --> 00:35:42,195
No!
[ Shouting Gibberish ]

329
00:35:42,270 --> 00:35:45,569
[ Creatures Laughing ]

330
00:35:45,640 --> 00:35:48,507
[ Gibberish Continues ]

331
00:35:51,780 --> 00:35:54,476
Damn it! Damn it!
Damn it!

332
00:35:54,549 --> 00:35:57,040
<i>Riddles! Riddles!
Riddles!</i>

333
00:35:57,118 --> 00:36:01,316
<i>Damn it! Riddles!
Riddles! Riddles!</i>

334
00:36:05,560 --> 00:36:07,494
Gump?

335
00:36:09,631 --> 00:36:11,565
Gump?

336
00:36:18,006 --> 00:36:20,975
Gump?

337
00:36:23,144 --> 00:36:25,874
You've bested me, Jack.

338
00:36:25,947 --> 00:36:29,178
Bested me, bested me.

339
00:36:29,251 --> 00:36:33,381
A riddle without an answer's
like an empty cup when
you're thirsty for wine.

340
00:36:33,455 --> 00:36:38,051
Well spoken!
And if it's wine you want,
it's wine we shall have.

341
00:36:38,126 --> 00:36:43,564
<i>Brown Tom! A small measure
of entertainment at best.</i>

342
00:36:43,632 --> 00:36:47,193
<i>[ Brown Tom ]
But, Gump, it's the last bottle
of me best wine.</i>

343
00:36:47,269 --> 00:36:50,170
Oh-Oh, if you say so, sir.

344
00:36:52,507 --> 00:36:54,441
Mmm.

345
00:36:58,580 --> 00:37:01,572
<i>Now, Gump, don't you
be forgetting me.</i>

346
00:37:02,884 --> 00:37:05,250
Oh, careful now.

347
00:37:05,320 --> 00:37:08,255
Oh, it's so precious.

348
00:37:08,323 --> 00:37:11,258
Elderberry wine.
[ Flatulence ]

349
00:37:11,326 --> 00:37:14,386
Sorry.
No finer drink
under heaven.

350
00:37:14,462 --> 00:37:16,794
Here's to Jack,
Oh, brother.

351
00:37:16,865 --> 00:37:21,529
riddle solver, dancing fool
and fairy friend.

352
00:37:21,603 --> 00:37:23,730
<i>Tip it.</i>

353
00:37:23,805 --> 00:37:26,774
Hmm. Ahhh.

354
00:37:29,210 --> 00:37:33,271
[ Sighs ]
Here, this'll help.

355
00:37:33,348 --> 00:37:35,612
Don't you care
what's happened?

356
00:37:35,684 --> 00:37:39,347
Of course we care.
What good's a world locked
in a season of death?

357
00:37:39,421 --> 00:37:41,946
<i>But we must find
the answer.
That we must.</i>

358
00:37:42,023 --> 00:37:45,754
But first we must see that
no harm's come to the Unicorn.

359
00:37:45,827 --> 00:37:48,591
<i>[ Brown Tom ]
l sadly fear the worst.</i>

360
00:37:48,663 --> 00:37:51,223
<i>[ Wolf Howling ]</i>

361
00:38:32,674 --> 00:38:36,269
<i>[ lndistinct Squealing ]
Wait. Shhh.</i>

362
00:38:42,684 --> 00:38:45,209
Lily!

363
00:38:46,855 --> 00:38:48,846
Jack, what?

364
00:39:39,607 --> 00:39:41,541
Jack!

365
00:40:11,739 --> 00:40:15,436
[ Unicorn Neighing ]

366
00:40:23,885 --> 00:40:25,944
[ Neighing ]

367
00:40:47,242 --> 00:40:50,006
[ Neighing Continues ]

368
00:41:23,611 --> 00:41:26,978
- [ Unicorn Squeals ]
- Forgive me.

369
00:41:31,553 --> 00:41:33,487
I meant no wrong.

370
00:41:35,657 --> 00:41:38,956
[ Whinnies ]

371
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:47,734
[ Neighs ]

372
00:41:51,239 --> 00:41:55,505
[ Neighing Continues ]

373
00:42:19,200 --> 00:42:23,637
Well, Jack, tell us
what has happened.

374
00:42:32,947 --> 00:42:37,577
Come on, Jack.
Don't keep us in the dark.

375
00:42:37,652 --> 00:42:40,917
The dark
is where we'll stay.

376
00:42:40,989 --> 00:42:42,923
We're cursed.

377
00:42:42,991 --> 00:42:46,654
<i>Is there naught
we can do?
[ Unicorn Neighing ]</i>

378
00:42:46,728 --> 00:42:49,253
We must get
the alicorn back.

379
00:42:50,732 --> 00:42:54,793
Only then will the world
return to normal.

380
00:42:54,869 --> 00:42:58,202
We must find a champion...

381
00:42:58,272 --> 00:43:01,503
bold of heart
and pure in spirit.

382
00:43:01,576 --> 00:43:04,443
<i>[ Brown Tom ]
Champion? What champion?</i>

383
00:43:04,512 --> 00:43:07,777
<i>[ Gump ]
Don't give up so quick, lads.</i>

384
00:43:07,849 --> 00:43:10,113
You'll do.

385
00:43:11,853 --> 00:43:14,447
We must get you
some weapons.

386
00:43:14,522 --> 00:43:17,047
But, Gump, I know
nothing of weapons.

387
00:43:17,125 --> 00:43:20,686
You'll learn. I know
where to find the best.

388
00:43:20,762 --> 00:43:24,630
<i>Brown Tom,
stay here with the Unicorn
and guard her well.</i>

389
00:43:24,699 --> 00:43:28,499
<i>Like me own life.
Better.
She's the last of her kind.</i>

390
00:43:28,569 --> 00:43:32,061
[ Sighs ]

391
00:43:39,113 --> 00:43:41,047
[ Whinnies ]

392
00:43:41,115 --> 00:43:44,141
Magic horn
is mine, mine, mine.

393
00:43:44,218 --> 00:43:47,619
Now all creatures
will love the night...

394
00:43:47,689 --> 00:43:50,123
and worship goblins
as divine.

395
00:43:50,191 --> 00:43:52,955
<i>You shouldn't
talk like that, Blix.</i>

396
00:43:53,027 --> 00:43:56,463
Why not?
I've got the power now.

397
00:43:56,531 --> 00:43:59,728
[ Squeals ]
Plenty big talk.

398
00:43:59,801 --> 00:44:02,201
Hah!
[ Laughing ]

399
00:44:02,270 --> 00:44:06,036
[ Indistinct Shouting ]

400
00:44:06,107 --> 00:44:09,201
[ Laughter, Chattering ]

401
00:44:09,277 --> 00:44:13,304
Not even darkness
lasts forever.

402
00:44:19,187 --> 00:44:22,588
Jack, I can't go
with you now.

403
00:44:22,657 --> 00:44:25,023
Anyway, Oona
will guide the way.

404
00:44:29,697 --> 00:44:33,861
Follow me, Jack.
Over here. Come on.

405
00:44:55,423 --> 00:44:57,391
Come on, Jack.

406
00:45:14,976 --> 00:45:17,672
<i>[ lndistinct Whisper ]</i>

407
00:45:19,480 --> 00:45:23,678
Here, Jack.
Come on.

408
00:45:47,175 --> 00:45:50,440
[ Jingling ]

409
00:45:53,581 --> 00:45:55,947
Oona.

410
00:45:57,318 --> 00:46:01,721
Nobody knows but you.
It's our secret, Jack.

411
00:46:01,789 --> 00:46:05,850
<i>Don't tell Gump. Promise?</i>

412
00:46:05,927 --> 00:46:08,259
<i>Promise!</i>

413
00:46:08,329 --> 00:46:11,526
<i>l could be anything
you want me to be,</i>

414
00:46:11,599 --> 00:46:14,534
<i>even your heart's desire.</i>

415
00:46:14,602 --> 00:46:17,696
<i>You've got to help us,Jack.</i>

416
00:46:17,772 --> 00:46:21,765
<i>The fairies'love
makes anything possible.</i>

417
00:46:31,252 --> 00:46:35,552
Higher, higher,
burning fire.

418
00:46:35,623 --> 00:46:39,491
<i>Making music like a choir.
[ Fiendish Laughing ]</i>

419
00:46:39,560 --> 00:46:41,687
It seems a pity
to waste such power.

420
00:46:41,762 --> 00:46:45,562
<i>Waste? Better watch out,
old pal Pox,</i>

421
00:46:45,633 --> 00:46:48,568
or I'll turn you
into little pork chops.

422
00:46:48,636 --> 00:46:51,537
Why not turn everything
into garbage?

423
00:46:51,606 --> 00:46:54,439
A great towering
mountain of slop.

424
00:46:54,508 --> 00:46:57,636
- Wouldn't that be magic?
- [ Laughing ]

425
00:46:57,712 --> 00:47:01,011
Higher, higher,
burning fire.

426
00:47:01,082 --> 00:47:05,246
<i>Making music like a choir.</i>

427
00:47:05,319 --> 00:47:08,982
<i>[ Fiendish Laughing Continues ]</i>

428
00:47:09,056 --> 00:47:12,355
<i>Blix, Blix. Blix!</i>

429
00:47:12,426 --> 00:47:15,054
- What?
- Big D.!

430
00:47:15,129 --> 00:47:18,895
[ Groaning ]

431
00:47:18,966 --> 00:47:21,093
Stop!
[ Coughs ]

432
00:47:21,168 --> 00:47:24,069
Hear me,
you angel of darkness!

433
00:47:24,138 --> 00:47:28,700
Your reign is over!
A new order begins!

434
00:47:28,776 --> 00:47:32,234
- I hold the power!
- Enough!

435
00:47:34,682 --> 00:47:39,915
<i>Shit! Please!
It was only a joke.</i>

436
00:47:39,987 --> 00:47:43,445
[ Groaning ]
I didn't mean it.

437
00:47:43,524 --> 00:47:46,459
No! No!

438
00:47:46,527 --> 00:47:48,791
Have you no sense of humor?

439
00:47:48,863 --> 00:47:50,854
<i>Adios, amigos!</i>

440
00:47:50,932 --> 00:47:54,459
<i>[ Screaming, Crashing ]</i>

441
00:47:54,535 --> 00:47:57,060
Wow.

442
00:47:57,138 --> 00:47:59,299
<i>Forgive that intrusion,
great lord,</i>

443
00:47:59,373 --> 00:48:02,570
<i>but goblins are inclined
to be outspoken.</i>

444
00:48:02,643 --> 00:48:04,770
Yeah.
and I like to encourage
their initiative.

445
00:48:04,845 --> 00:48:08,144
Did you think
this a mere plaything?

446
00:48:08,215 --> 00:48:11,776
<i>With it,
my empire is eternal.</i>

447
00:48:11,852 --> 00:48:14,446
<i>Before l ruled
only the night.</i>

448
00:48:14,522 --> 00:48:19,960
Now my minions
will frolic in darkness
until the end of time.

449
00:48:20,027 --> 00:48:23,053
[ Chuckling ]

450
00:48:23,130 --> 00:48:25,621
The Unicorns are dead,
is this not true?

451
00:48:25,700 --> 00:48:29,500
True, lord,
very plenty true.
Undeniably true.

452
00:48:29,570 --> 00:48:33,438
You lie!
Here is dawn!

453
00:48:33,507 --> 00:48:36,305
<i>lt is essentially true.
On the other hand--</i>

454
00:48:36,377 --> 00:48:39,744
Stallion is dead.
Dead as dreams.

455
00:48:39,814 --> 00:48:42,874
- Out with it!
- The mare lives still!

456
00:48:42,950 --> 00:48:47,148
<i>lf even one Unicorn
walks the earth,
my power is not complete.</i>

457
00:48:47,221 --> 00:48:50,156
<i>She's just a female, lord.
She has no power.</i>

458
00:48:50,224 --> 00:48:53,193
Only the power of creation.

459
00:48:53,260 --> 00:48:56,127
Get the mare!

460
00:48:56,197 --> 00:48:59,189
I command you!

461
00:49:02,636 --> 00:49:05,434
Well, let's see,
what have we here?

462
00:49:05,506 --> 00:49:09,738
<i>Ahh, a little sassafras.
[ Unicorn Whinnies ]</i>

463
00:49:09,810 --> 00:49:12,040
<i>A little spearmint
would be nice, huh?</i>

464
00:49:12,113 --> 00:49:14,673
<i>Some fox glove?</i>

465
00:49:14,749 --> 00:49:18,742
And a little colt's foot.
[ Chuckles ]

466
00:49:18,819 --> 00:49:20,753
<i>[ Crying ]
[ Unicorn Neighing ]</i>

467
00:49:20,821 --> 00:49:23,915
Hey, who goes there, what?

468
00:49:23,991 --> 00:49:27,757
[ Neighing Continues ]

469
00:49:27,828 --> 00:49:30,524
I'm-- I'm Princess Lily.

470
00:49:30,598 --> 00:49:33,692
You! You're the cause
of all our sorrow.

471
00:49:33,768 --> 00:49:37,670
[ Crying Continues ]
I'm-- I'm so sorry.

472
00:49:37,738 --> 00:49:43,267
I didn't know.
Please, please forgive me.

473
00:49:43,344 --> 00:49:46,472
- I'm not the one
you should be askin'.
- Listen to me.

474
00:49:46,547 --> 00:49:50,881
Try and understand.
I'm only trying
to make things right.

475
00:49:50,951 --> 00:49:53,886
Darkness has sent the goblins
back for the mare.

476
00:49:53,954 --> 00:49:58,357
It's not safe to stay here.
You'll have to hurry!
Leave now! Go!

477
00:49:58,426 --> 00:50:01,224
Good lass. You're
a plucky little partridge.

478
00:50:01,295 --> 00:50:04,389
- Hurry! Aaah!
- Too late!

479
00:50:04,465 --> 00:50:07,798
You imps are lookin'
for a fight, you come to
the chap who'll oblige ya.

480
00:50:07,868 --> 00:50:10,530
[ Growls ]

481
00:50:10,604 --> 00:50:13,732
Ooh! Ah! Ah!

482
00:50:13,808 --> 00:50:17,403
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Unicorn Neighing ]

483
00:50:17,478 --> 00:50:19,605
- Try this on for size.
- [ Lily Screams ]

484
00:50:19,680 --> 00:50:22,615
You can't beat me.
Ha-ha, look at that!

485
00:50:22,683 --> 00:50:25,584
<i>Keep 'em coming, fellas!
Ha-ha!</i>

486
00:50:25,653 --> 00:50:30,556
Oh, check this out!
Yes, sir. You see?

487
00:50:30,624 --> 00:50:35,186
<i>You just can't beat me!
You can't--</i>

488
00:50:35,262 --> 00:50:39,756
Little tool is stuck.
They done for me.

489
00:50:39,834 --> 00:50:43,326
[ Growling ]

490
00:50:43,404 --> 00:50:46,430
[ Neighing Continues ]

491
00:50:52,079 --> 00:50:54,013
Quick!

492
00:50:57,284 --> 00:50:59,946
Wait for me!
[ Panting ]

493
00:51:04,225 --> 00:51:06,250
Brown Tom!

494
00:51:10,364 --> 00:51:14,630
Brown Tom,
you can't be dead.

495
00:51:14,702 --> 00:51:17,170
<i>This is terrible.
Terrible!</i>

496
00:51:17,238 --> 00:51:20,230
<i>Brown Tom.
Brown Tom.</i>

497
00:51:20,307 --> 00:51:22,332
Gump?

498
00:51:22,409 --> 00:51:24,536
Screwball.

499
00:51:24,612 --> 00:51:27,137
Jack, lad.

500
00:51:27,214 --> 00:51:31,742
- They killed you too?
- Of course they didn't.

501
00:51:31,819 --> 00:51:35,619
- But what in blazes
are you talking about?
- Goblins.

502
00:51:35,689 --> 00:51:39,056
- Goblins?
- Shot me through me brain pan.

503
00:51:39,126 --> 00:51:41,492
Oh.
[ Groans, Chuckles ]

504
00:51:41,562 --> 00:51:44,224
That's one spot an arrow
will do no harm.

505
00:51:44,298 --> 00:51:48,826
<i>l did my best to fight 'em off,
but they swarmed up
by the hundreds.</i>

506
00:51:48,903 --> 00:51:53,738
<i>All fierce creatures they were.
The princess warned me, but--</i>

507
00:51:53,807 --> 00:51:55,798
Lily?
Aye.

508
00:51:55,876 --> 00:51:57,810
Then she's alive!

509
00:51:57,878 --> 00:52:00,813
She was alive still
when they killed me.

510
00:52:00,881 --> 00:52:03,509
The goblins
must have taken her.

511
00:52:03,584 --> 00:52:05,017
<i>[ Gump ]
We follow their tracks
in the snow.</i>

512
00:52:10,624 --> 00:52:12,888
The Great Tree.

513
00:52:12,960 --> 00:52:16,191
<i>When evil anarchy
ruled the land,</i>

514
00:52:16,263 --> 00:52:19,494
<i>the wicked came here
to sacrifice.</i>

515
00:52:33,347 --> 00:52:37,579
<i>[ Birds Squawking ]</i>

516
00:52:52,766 --> 00:52:56,395
Ugly. I hate it.

517
00:52:56,470 --> 00:52:59,098
Good. You go first.

518
00:52:59,173 --> 00:53:01,698
Why always me?

519
00:53:01,775 --> 00:53:04,335
Go!

520
00:53:04,411 --> 00:53:07,505
[ Groaning ]

521
00:53:07,581 --> 00:53:10,573
[ Muttering ]
Foreigner.

522
00:53:10,651 --> 00:53:15,145
[ Muttering Continues ]
Ooh, slippery.

523
00:53:21,562 --> 00:53:24,122
Uh, uh--

524
00:53:24,198 --> 00:53:26,962
Oh, okay, okay.

525
00:53:27,034 --> 00:53:30,128
[ Muttering Continues ]

526
00:53:38,012 --> 00:53:40,173
<i>[ Squeals ]
l made it!</i>

527
00:53:40,247 --> 00:53:43,182
<i>[ Gump ]
Screwball!</i>

528
00:53:49,523 --> 00:53:53,823
- [ Gasping ]
- [ Shrieking ]

529
00:53:55,329 --> 00:53:57,923
Foul-tasting fairy!

530
00:54:03,170 --> 00:54:06,537
<i>Come to Meg, juicy boy.</i>

531
00:54:08,776 --> 00:54:11,574
[ Shrieks ]

532
00:54:11,645 --> 00:54:15,547
Who be this tender morsel...

533
00:54:15,616 --> 00:54:20,383
disturbing
Meg Mucklebone's rest?

534
00:54:20,454 --> 00:54:24,515
<i>Jack.
They call me Jack, ma'am.</i>

535
00:54:24,591 --> 00:54:27,526
[ Squeals ]

536
00:54:27,594 --> 00:54:31,894
And what a fine,
fat boy you are, Jack.

537
00:54:31,965 --> 00:54:34,297
You don't really mean
to eat me, do you, ma'am?

538
00:54:34,368 --> 00:54:37,826
Oh, indeed I do!
[ Cackling ]

539
00:54:37,905 --> 00:54:39,805
[ Cackling Continues ]

540
00:54:39,873 --> 00:54:43,400
But that would be a shame,
because someone as fair...

541
00:54:43,477 --> 00:54:47,743
and lovely as yourself,
Miss Meg, deserves far better
than scrawny me.

542
00:54:50,217 --> 00:54:52,811
Don't you think?

543
00:54:52,886 --> 00:54:58,518
You think me fair,
do you, Jack?

544
00:54:58,592 --> 00:55:02,653
<i>All the heavenly angels
must envy your beauty.</i>

545
00:55:02,730 --> 00:55:05,722
[ Giggling ]

546
00:55:10,871 --> 00:55:13,499
What a fine meal
you'll make,

547
00:55:13,574 --> 00:55:17,635
be the rest of you
as sweet as your tongue.

548
00:55:17,711 --> 00:55:19,736
- [ Cackling ]
- Wait! No!

549
00:55:19,813 --> 00:55:24,045
Your Loveliness,
feast on the beauty
of your reflection.

550
00:55:24,118 --> 00:55:27,610
You are an angel, Miss Meg.

551
00:55:27,688 --> 00:55:31,055
<i>Look. Look.
Ohhh.</i>

552
00:55:31,125 --> 00:55:33,753
What a splendid idea.

553
00:55:36,330 --> 00:55:38,025
[ Yells ]

554
00:55:39,266 --> 00:55:41,200
Clever boy!

555
00:55:41,268 --> 00:55:45,432
[ Evil Laughter ]
Yes.

556
00:55:45,506 --> 00:55:49,772
<i>Your alchemy makes
crusted steel shine like silver.
[ Whining ]</i>

557
00:55:51,044 --> 00:55:53,137
That's discerning taste...

558
00:55:53,213 --> 00:55:56,239
for one so young, Jack.

559
00:55:58,185 --> 00:56:01,621
[ Whining Continues ]

560
00:56:02,689 --> 00:56:06,147
<i>Come. Come,Jack!</i>

561
00:56:06,226 --> 00:56:09,252
Give us a kiss...
before dining!

562
00:56:09,329 --> 00:56:12,560
- [ Grunting ]
- [ Screaming ]

563
00:56:25,846 --> 00:56:28,440
I did it!
[ Panting ]

564
00:56:29,516 --> 00:56:32,451
[ Birds Croaking ]

565
00:57:24,371 --> 00:57:27,204
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]

566
00:57:47,661 --> 00:57:49,595
- [ Screaming ]
- Screwball!

567
00:57:49,663 --> 00:57:51,426
[ Mumbling ]

568
00:57:54,368 --> 00:57:56,962
[ Mumbling Continues ]

569
00:57:57,037 --> 00:58:00,029
Oh, okay. Okay.

570
00:58:00,107 --> 00:58:03,907
Oh! Whee! Look.

571
00:58:03,977 --> 00:58:07,538
What a big trumpet!
I'll bet it makes a lot of noise.

572
00:58:07,614 --> 00:58:10,344
[ Whispering ]
Our lives are lost if it blows.

573
00:58:14,154 --> 00:58:16,088
Hmm.

574
00:58:18,125 --> 00:58:21,151
Mm-hmm.

575
00:58:21,228 --> 00:58:24,163
<i>[ Arrow Clattering
To Unknown Depth ]</i>

576
00:58:25,799 --> 00:58:29,963
Mm-hmm.
[ Grunting ]

577
00:58:30,037 --> 00:58:32,597
Oh!

578
00:58:35,242 --> 00:58:37,608
I think it stopped.

579
00:58:37,678 --> 00:58:40,943
[ All Shouting ]

580
00:58:42,716 --> 00:58:44,980
[ Shouting Continues ]
Look out!

581
00:58:51,391 --> 00:58:53,791
[ Grunting, Shouting ]

582
00:58:53,860 --> 00:58:56,158
<i>[ Brown Tom ]
My back! Me achin'back!</i>

583
00:58:56,229 --> 00:59:00,097
Oh, I'm not as old
as I used to be, you know.

584
00:59:00,167 --> 00:59:02,362
<i>[ Clattering ]</i>

585
00:59:02,436 --> 00:59:06,532
<i>[ Rumbling ]
Ooh. Hey, where are we?</i>

586
00:59:06,607 --> 00:59:09,542
Someplace
we don't want to be.

587
00:59:11,011 --> 00:59:12,979
[ Mutters, Indistinct ]

588
00:59:13,046 --> 00:59:16,447
Hey, hey!
Wait for me!

589
00:59:16,516 --> 00:59:20,316
We gotta get out of here!
It's the stench of hell itself!

590
00:59:22,356 --> 00:59:25,189
Shh! Quiet!

591
00:59:25,258 --> 00:59:29,558
You'll be fricasseed fairies
if you don't keep quiet.

592
00:59:29,630 --> 00:59:31,894
Who be you, bucket head?

593
00:59:31,965 --> 00:59:35,264
Who I am won't help me
nor you, neither,

594
00:59:35,335 --> 00:59:38,634
even though
we are all brothers.

595
00:59:38,705 --> 00:59:40,639
<i>[ Screwball Shouts ]</i>

596
00:59:42,309 --> 00:59:44,800
[ Giggles ]
What happened to you?

597
00:59:44,878 --> 00:59:46,812
It's a long story.

598
00:59:46,880 --> 00:59:50,008
<i>Let's just say
I went looking for adventure...</i>

599
00:59:50,083 --> 00:59:53,143
<i>and found
more than l could handle.</i>

600
00:59:53,220 --> 00:59:56,849
<i>Doesn't matter now anyway.</i>

601
00:59:56,923 --> 01:00:00,188
<i>We are all in the same fix!</i>

602
01:00:01,528 --> 01:00:05,259
I knew it. I knew it.
I should have stayed at home.

603
01:00:05,332 --> 01:00:07,698
<i>Let's face it, brothers.</i>

604
01:00:07,768 --> 01:00:12,796
Me and you all...
is barbecue.

605
01:00:12,873 --> 01:00:16,309
[ Mutters ]

606
01:00:16,376 --> 01:00:19,368
Barbecue?
That's right. Barbecue.

607
01:00:19,446 --> 01:00:22,347
Only dead meat waits
for the stew pot.

608
01:00:24,184 --> 01:00:26,846
Spring the lock
with your magic, Gump.

609
01:00:39,266 --> 01:00:41,200
Ooh!
Ah!

610
01:00:42,903 --> 01:00:45,098
Iron is trouble for elves.

611
01:00:45,172 --> 01:00:47,106
Iron, huh?

612
01:00:50,077 --> 01:00:52,671
Oh!

613
01:00:52,746 --> 01:00:57,649
[ Growling ]

614
01:01:03,323 --> 01:01:05,154
Oh, no!

615
01:01:07,227 --> 01:01:09,161
The thing!

616
01:01:09,229 --> 01:01:12,323
<i>[ Groaning, Laughing ]</i>

617
01:01:12,399 --> 01:01:15,800
Oh, no!
He's coming! Hide!

618
01:01:15,869 --> 01:01:17,336
Hide!
Hide! Hide!

619
01:01:17,404 --> 01:01:19,463
[ Sniffing ]

620
01:01:19,539 --> 01:01:22,337
- Oh!
- [ Growling ]

621
01:01:22,409 --> 01:01:24,934
<i>[ Evil Laughter ]</i>

622
01:01:25,011 --> 01:01:27,070
I don't think I can handle it!
Help me!

623
01:01:28,448 --> 01:01:30,609
[ Shouting ]

624
01:01:33,720 --> 01:01:37,178
[ Laughing Continues ]

625
01:01:55,909 --> 01:01:59,743
[ Shouting ]

626
01:01:59,813 --> 01:02:03,510
<i>[ Screaming ]
Let me go! Let me go!</i>

627
01:02:03,583 --> 01:02:07,781
Help! Help me!

628
01:02:09,256 --> 01:02:11,121
Please! Please!

629
01:02:11,191 --> 01:02:13,625
Help me!

630
01:02:13,693 --> 01:02:17,356
Oh, you beast!
Help me!

631
01:02:17,430 --> 01:02:21,025
[ Screaming ]
[ Shouting Continues ]

632
01:02:24,371 --> 01:02:28,535
<i>[ Screaming, Shouting Continue ]
Let me go!</i>

633
01:02:30,477 --> 01:02:33,241
<i>Ah... ah... ah...</i>

634
01:02:33,313 --> 01:02:36,009
<i>ah... ah... achoo!</i>

635
01:02:37,484 --> 01:02:40,248
Gump, we've got to help him.

636
01:02:40,320 --> 01:02:43,255
Oh, don't worry.
Our brother can take care
of himself.

637
01:02:43,323 --> 01:02:46,292
I'm sure of it,
I think.

638
01:02:46,359 --> 01:02:50,022
Screwball's right.
It's more important
that you find the Unicorn.

639
01:02:50,096 --> 01:02:53,532
Why not have Oona fly out,
find a key?

640
01:02:54,668 --> 01:02:58,035
<i>Oona?
But she's much too small.</i>

641
01:02:58,104 --> 01:03:00,072
Could never lift it.

642
01:03:01,441 --> 01:03:02,806
<i>Our secret!</i>

643
01:03:02,876 --> 01:03:05,538
Our secret will keep forever
in this grave if you don't help us.

644
01:03:05,612 --> 01:03:08,672
- You promised!
- [ Hisses ]

645
01:03:08,748 --> 01:03:12,844
You willful sprite.
How dare you keep such secrets?

646
01:03:12,919 --> 01:03:15,251
They're mine to keep.

647
01:03:20,427 --> 01:03:25,626
I'll do what you ask...
if you'll kiss me, Jack.

648
01:03:35,108 --> 01:03:37,042
Easy enough.

649
01:03:41,848 --> 01:03:43,213
[ Chuckles ]

650
01:03:43,283 --> 01:03:47,879
You call that a kiss?
Am I not sweet?

651
01:03:51,091 --> 01:03:54,060
Sweeter than bee pollen...

652
01:03:54,127 --> 01:03:56,095
on a summer wind.

653
01:03:57,797 --> 01:04:01,255
Sweet as the wind
that blows me to you.

654
01:04:03,236 --> 01:04:07,502
[ Gasping ]
Oh, it's fairy magic.

655
01:04:08,708 --> 01:04:11,108
Lily?

656
01:04:11,177 --> 01:04:15,614
- Lily?
- Yes, Jack.

657
01:04:23,823 --> 01:04:26,314
This isn't real.

658
01:04:26,393 --> 01:04:29,157
Oh, it is.

659
01:04:29,229 --> 01:04:32,130
I'm warm and alive...

660
01:04:32,198 --> 01:04:34,632
and want to be in your arms.

661
01:04:58,024 --> 01:05:01,152
No, I, I can't. No.

662
01:05:01,227 --> 01:05:03,661
<i>This is just
more fairy glamour.</i>

663
01:05:06,066 --> 01:05:09,524
Human hearts
don't work that way.

664
01:05:09,602 --> 01:05:12,127
What care I
for human hearts?

665
01:05:12,205 --> 01:05:15,265
Soft and spiritless
as porridge!

666
01:05:15,342 --> 01:05:18,971
A fairy's heart beats
fierce and free!

667
01:05:22,716 --> 01:05:25,514
[ Whimpering ]

668
01:05:25,585 --> 01:05:29,453
<i>[ Jack ]
Oona!</i>

669
01:05:29,522 --> 01:05:33,754
Your fine sensibilities
have left us here to rot!

670
01:05:33,827 --> 01:05:36,591
<i>[ Brown Tom ]
l'm behind you all the way, Gump.</i>

671
01:05:41,034 --> 01:05:44,765
You look like mourners
at your own funeral.

672
01:05:48,308 --> 01:05:51,277
Oona!

673
01:05:51,344 --> 01:05:53,744
[ Snaps Fingers ]

674
01:05:56,916 --> 01:05:59,783
<i>[ Gate Creaks ]
Quick, lads!</i>

675
01:06:05,158 --> 01:06:07,786
<i>You!</i>

676
01:06:07,861 --> 01:06:11,353
You mortal, you!

677
01:06:11,431 --> 01:06:16,198
<i>I could vex you!
Dance your life away!</i>

678
01:06:31,284 --> 01:06:33,946
Uh, I'll stay here and--

679
01:06:34,020 --> 01:06:36,818
- Ahh! Wait for me!
- [ Creature Howls ]

680
01:06:36,890 --> 01:06:39,484
[ Mumbling, Shouting ]

681
01:06:52,806 --> 01:06:57,869
[ Screwball ]
A terrible sight
for a sober man.

682
01:07:06,986 --> 01:07:11,218
Shh!
We must find the dungeons.

683
01:07:11,291 --> 01:07:15,227
[ Nervous Laugh ]
I think I'll stay right here,
thank you very much.

684
01:07:15,295 --> 01:07:17,229
You'll search
with the rest of us.

685
01:07:17,297 --> 01:07:19,731
Then I'll go with Jack.
No! We split up.

686
01:07:19,799 --> 01:07:22,233
Yes! It's better
if we go in teams.

687
01:07:22,302 --> 01:07:25,066
- No, I will go with Ja--
- Shh!

688
01:07:25,138 --> 01:07:27,470
Gump and me,
Brown Tom and Screwball.

689
01:07:27,540 --> 01:07:29,474
Right. Let's synchronize.

690
01:07:29,542 --> 01:07:32,705
Oh!
[ Chuckles ]

691
01:07:32,779 --> 01:07:36,078
[ Grunting ]

692
01:07:37,383 --> 01:07:41,046
Oh! A-ha!

693
01:07:41,121 --> 01:07:46,058
We meet back here in twice
500 beats of a bluebird's heart.

694
01:07:46,126 --> 01:07:49,391
Do you know what I think?
I think we should add a couple
more hundred breaths of a--

695
01:07:49,462 --> 01:07:51,453
Shh!

696
01:07:52,532 --> 01:07:54,830
Take care.
Come on, Jack.

697
01:07:57,937 --> 01:07:59,871
Be careful.

698
01:08:04,677 --> 01:08:08,841
There's only one thing
I want to know.
What?

699
01:08:08,915 --> 01:08:11,281
[ Crying ]
Why me?
Shh!

700
01:08:11,351 --> 01:08:14,912
I think we should go west.
I think we should go east.

701
01:08:14,988 --> 01:08:16,922
Oh, okay.
Wait!

702
01:08:19,192 --> 01:08:23,925
<i>[ Lord of Darkness ]
Father, l hold the world
in my grasp,</i>

703
01:08:23,997 --> 01:08:29,401
<i>and yet this girl...
distracts me.</i>

704
01:08:29,469 --> 01:08:33,701
<i>lt has been an eternity
since l felt such desire.</i>

705
01:08:33,773 --> 01:08:36,241
<i>What am l to do?</i>

706
01:08:36,309 --> 01:08:41,941
<i>She fascinates you
because her soul is pure.</i>

707
01:08:42,015 --> 01:08:44,882
<i>l'll take her then.
Fool!</i>

708
01:08:44,951 --> 01:08:49,820
<i>You must woo her!</i>

709
01:08:50,890 --> 01:08:55,691
She remembers the world
as it was,

710
01:08:55,762 --> 01:08:58,856
so... tempt her.

711
01:08:58,932 --> 01:09:02,095
Win her.

712
01:09:02,168 --> 01:09:06,195
<i>Make her one of us.</i>

713
01:09:19,652 --> 01:09:23,486
Hmm. Hey. Psst!

714
01:09:23,556 --> 01:09:26,491
Psst! Psst!

715
01:09:26,559 --> 01:09:28,493
Did, did you see something?

716
01:09:28,561 --> 01:09:31,689
No, did you?
I don't know.

717
01:09:31,764 --> 01:09:33,698
I think.

718
01:10:23,149 --> 01:10:26,084
<i>[ Evil Laughter ]</i>

719
01:10:41,601 --> 01:10:44,035
<i>[ Heavy Breathing ]</i>

720
01:11:16,769 --> 01:11:18,703
[ Muttering ]

721
01:11:18,771 --> 01:11:21,205
<i>D-D-D-Did you hear that?</i>

722
01:11:21,274 --> 01:11:23,208
<i>[ Neighing ]
What's that?</i>

723
01:11:23,276 --> 01:11:25,210
That's a horse,
you idiot.

724
01:11:32,185 --> 01:11:36,349
<i>[ Faint Voice ]
Woo her.</i>

725
01:11:36,422 --> 01:11:39,289
<i>Woo her.</i>

726
01:12:08,688 --> 01:12:11,350
<i>[ Faint Breathing ]</i>

727
01:12:18,030 --> 01:12:21,295
<i>Win her.</i>

728
01:12:25,405 --> 01:12:30,399
[ Tinkling ]

729
01:13:27,300 --> 01:13:30,929
<i>Woo her, win her.</i>

730
01:13:31,003 --> 01:13:32,937
<i>[ Gasps ]</i>

731
01:13:55,995 --> 01:13:59,795
Make her one of us.

732
01:16:07,760 --> 01:16:09,352
[ Gasps ]

733
01:16:46,766 --> 01:16:49,530
<i>[ Footsteps Approaching ]</i>

734
01:17:11,323 --> 01:17:13,382
[ Gasps ]

735
01:17:17,797 --> 01:17:22,393
<i>Lady, do not be afraid.</i>

736
01:17:22,468 --> 01:17:27,735
Quiet, quiet.

737
01:17:29,508 --> 01:17:32,568
How like you my gifts?

738
01:17:32,645 --> 01:17:36,342
Does the gown
not please you?

739
01:17:37,883 --> 01:17:40,477
[ Crying ]
No.

740
01:17:40,553 --> 01:17:42,487
[ Laughs ]

741
01:17:42,555 --> 01:17:46,958
Can you speak so
of your bridal gown?

742
01:17:47,026 --> 01:17:49,586
I've found my true mate,

743
01:17:49,662 --> 01:17:52,187
and you know it.

744
01:17:52,264 --> 01:17:57,861
- Never.
- Beneath the skin,
we are already one.

745
01:18:00,606 --> 01:18:03,370
<i>Was it not your sin
trapped the Unicorn?</i>

746
01:18:03,442 --> 01:18:06,138
- No.
- Even now...

747
01:18:06,212 --> 01:18:08,908
the evil seed
of what you have done...

748
01:18:08,981 --> 01:18:12,382
germinates within you.

749
01:18:12,451 --> 01:18:14,544
<i>No. You lie.</i>

750
01:18:14,620 --> 01:18:18,112
You disgust me.

751
01:18:18,190 --> 01:18:20,124
You're nothing
but an animal.

752
01:18:20,192 --> 01:18:23,787
[ Evil Laughter ]

753
01:18:23,863 --> 01:18:27,629
We are all animals,
my lady.

754
01:18:27,700 --> 01:18:31,067
Most are too afraid
to see it.

755
01:18:32,471 --> 01:18:34,405
[ Laughter Continues ]

756
01:18:43,149 --> 01:18:46,141
<i>[ Laughter Continues ]</i>

757
01:18:48,087 --> 01:18:49,577
- Lily!
-Jack.

758
01:18:49,655 --> 01:18:53,216
<i>There's nothing
you can do now to help her.</i>

759
01:18:53,292 --> 01:18:55,886
Be thankful she still lives.

760
01:18:55,961 --> 01:18:57,895
<i>[ Oona ]
You've got to help us,
Jack.</i>

761
01:18:57,963 --> 01:19:02,059
<i>The last Unicorn dies
tonight.</i>

762
01:19:03,736 --> 01:19:06,637
<i>- As her blood ebbs,
- [ Whispers ] Never.</i>

763
01:19:06,705 --> 01:19:09,902
the sun sets forever.

764
01:19:09,975 --> 01:19:15,379
<i>There shall never be
another dawn.</i>

765
01:19:15,447 --> 01:19:17,677
<i>[ Lily ]
No!
[ Evil Laughter ]</i>

766
01:19:17,750 --> 01:19:23,245
<i>Lady, l require the solace
of the shadows...</i>

767
01:19:23,322 --> 01:19:27,258
and the dark of the night.

768
01:19:27,326 --> 01:19:31,786
Sunshine is my destroyer!

769
01:19:31,864 --> 01:19:34,355
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

770
01:19:38,237 --> 01:19:40,603
Damn you!
[ Grunts ]

771
01:19:40,673 --> 01:19:44,803
We are all of us damned,
my queen.

772
01:19:44,877 --> 01:19:46,435
[ Laughing ]

773
01:19:47,980 --> 01:19:50,813
As long as the sun still shines,

774
01:19:50,883 --> 01:19:53,875
we can destroy him.

775
01:19:53,953 --> 01:19:56,649
Let me dazzle you
with my wisdom.

776
01:19:59,191 --> 01:20:01,125
I think I know a way.

777
01:20:05,965 --> 01:20:09,230
Come on, come on, come on.
You're holding us up.

778
01:20:09,301 --> 01:20:12,532
Listen. We're not going down
the same corridor umpteen times.

779
01:20:12,605 --> 01:20:14,937
I think we should go that way.
No, we're going this way.

780
01:20:15,007 --> 01:20:16,941
No, not me.

781
01:20:21,313 --> 01:20:24,578
Let's go down there.
Stay close to me now.

782
01:20:24,650 --> 01:20:27,915
<i>[ Creature Wailing ]</i>

783
01:20:33,225 --> 01:20:35,989
[ Shouting, Indistinct ]

784
01:20:40,766 --> 01:20:42,700
You know what?
What?

785
01:20:42,768 --> 01:20:45,794
I vote we run like hell.
I second the motion.

786
01:20:45,871 --> 01:20:48,601
[ Screams ]

787
01:20:48,674 --> 01:20:50,642
[ Whispering ]
Screwball.

788
01:20:51,777 --> 01:20:53,369
[ Chuckles ]

789
01:20:54,446 --> 01:20:56,380
[ Gump ]
Where were you?

790
01:20:56,448 --> 01:21:00,748
In another three flicks
of a badger's tail,
we would have gone.

791
01:21:00,819 --> 01:21:03,481
While you're having fun,
time goes by fast.

792
01:21:03,555 --> 01:21:07,321
Yeah, we found the mare,
and it's alive in the dungeon.

793
01:21:07,393 --> 01:21:09,361
<i>Excellent.
Excellent, you two!</i>

794
01:21:09,428 --> 01:21:11,658
Thank you very much.

795
01:21:11,730 --> 01:21:14,563
<i>Now Jack has a plan,
and a good one!</i>

796
01:21:14,633 --> 01:21:18,069
<i>We must gather every
shining object we can find.</i>

797
01:21:18,137 --> 01:21:21,903
We're going to bring light
to darkness.

798
01:21:21,974 --> 01:21:24,408
[ Snoring ]

799
01:21:38,357 --> 01:21:40,917
[ Snoring Continues ]

800
01:21:46,999 --> 01:21:48,933
[ Buzz ]

801
01:21:54,606 --> 01:21:57,575
[ Muffled Cries ]
[ Banging On Pot ]

802
01:21:57,643 --> 01:21:59,577
Blunder.

803
01:22:05,784 --> 01:22:07,718
[ Snores ]

804
01:22:16,328 --> 01:22:18,819
Blunder!

805
01:22:18,897 --> 01:22:21,024
[ Muffled Cries Continue ]
Shh!

806
01:22:21,100 --> 01:22:23,796
Any more noise,
and you're shish kebab.

807
01:22:23,869 --> 01:22:26,565
You do what we say, understand?
Swear it.

808
01:22:26,638 --> 01:22:28,572
[ Mutters ]

809
01:22:28,640 --> 01:22:31,438
I swear it on the festering
forelock of Nicodemus!

810
01:22:31,510 --> 01:22:35,310
Please, help. Help me.

811
01:22:38,017 --> 01:22:39,951
Thank you.

812
01:22:43,956 --> 01:22:47,289
<i>[ Lord of Darkness ]
Judge me not so harshly,
mistress.</i>

813
01:22:47,359 --> 01:22:50,453
<i>l invite you
to share this supper.</i>

814
01:22:50,529 --> 01:22:53,760
<i>Look how sweet it is.</i>

815
01:23:56,462 --> 01:23:59,829
Hurry, hurry.
Keep 'em comin'!
Come on, come on!

816
01:24:17,316 --> 01:24:20,285
- Ow!
- [ Loud Clattering ]

817
01:24:20,352 --> 01:24:25,016
[ Grunting, Yelling ]

818
01:24:25,090 --> 01:24:27,081
- Brown Tom!
- Huh?

819
01:24:46,612 --> 01:24:49,445
[ Grunting ]

820
01:24:49,515 --> 01:24:51,949
[ Yelling ]

821
01:24:57,689 --> 01:24:59,714
[ Grunting, Shouting Continue ]

822
01:25:28,887 --> 01:25:30,787
<i>[ Screaming ]</i>

823
01:25:30,856 --> 01:25:34,189
[ Grunting, Shouting Continue ]

824
01:25:43,535 --> 01:25:46,368
[ Shouting Continues ]

825
01:25:49,107 --> 01:25:51,701
[ Rat Squealing ]

826
01:26:08,460 --> 01:26:11,725
<i>Gump? Gump!</i>

827
01:26:14,099 --> 01:26:18,536
<i>Gump?
Jack.Jack!</i>

828
01:26:23,675 --> 01:26:25,768
Three cheers
for our champion!

829
01:26:25,844 --> 01:26:27,209
Hip hip!
Hooray!

830
01:26:27,279 --> 01:26:29,543
<i>- Hip hip!
-Hooray!</i>

831
01:26:29,615 --> 01:26:31,310
Hip hip!
Hooray!
[ Laughs ]

832
01:26:57,009 --> 01:26:59,102
Now what, Jack?

833
01:26:59,177 --> 01:27:01,270
<i>[ Jack ]
Must go all the way out.</i>

834
01:27:03,982 --> 01:27:05,916
Light.

835
01:27:08,120 --> 01:27:10,054
Not much to hold on to.

836
01:27:10,122 --> 01:27:13,285
<i>Take a pea pod pixie
to make that climb.</i>

837
01:27:19,798 --> 01:27:21,732
I'll do it.

838
01:27:24,469 --> 01:27:27,131
<i>What's the matter?
Ain't I small enough
for the job?</i>

839
01:27:27,205 --> 01:27:30,572
<i>No job is too small
for my little brother.</i>

840
01:27:30,642 --> 01:27:34,578
Please, Gump. Let me try.
I won't let you down.

841
01:27:36,315 --> 01:27:38,806
All right, all right.
Do it, but be swift!

842
01:27:38,884 --> 01:27:42,411
Oh, thank you, thank you.
You'll never regret it.

843
01:27:42,487 --> 01:27:46,480
I always knew you'd
be going places, Screwball.
Yes.

844
01:27:52,030 --> 01:27:53,964
Uh--
[ Stammers ]

845
01:27:54,466 --> 01:27:56,229
- Eat.
- I'm not hungry.

846
01:27:56,301 --> 01:27:59,031
You lie.

847
01:27:59,104 --> 01:28:00,969
[ Laughing ]

848
01:28:01,039 --> 01:28:03,132
Just to please me.

849
01:28:03,208 --> 01:28:05,676
I do nothing
for your pleasure.

850
01:28:09,581 --> 01:28:11,515
All I wish...

851
01:28:11,583 --> 01:28:15,747
is for you to sit
and talk with me.

852
01:28:15,821 --> 01:28:18,153
Sit?

853
01:28:20,859 --> 01:28:23,726
- Here?
- Yes.

854
01:28:23,795 --> 01:28:25,729
Please.

855
01:28:25,797 --> 01:28:28,425
- I prefer to stand.
- Sit!

856
01:28:28,500 --> 01:28:32,300
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

857
01:28:32,371 --> 01:28:35,807
Or stand.
As you wish.

858
01:28:35,874 --> 01:28:40,504
<i>lt is enough that
we are alone together.</i>

859
01:28:42,247 --> 01:28:44,181
Just the two of us.

860
01:28:48,620 --> 01:28:53,319
Some... simple conversation.

861
01:28:54,459 --> 01:28:57,257
I have nothing
to talk about.

862
01:28:58,330 --> 01:29:01,561
You've stolen my dreams away.

863
01:29:01,633 --> 01:29:03,726
All things change, Lady.

864
01:29:05,604 --> 01:29:08,164
The dreams of youth...

865
01:29:08,240 --> 01:29:11,403
are the regrets of maturity.

866
01:29:14,079 --> 01:29:17,242
Dreams are my specialty.

867
01:29:17,315 --> 01:29:21,251
<i>Through dreams
l influence mankind.</i>

868
01:29:21,319 --> 01:29:24,413
My dream...

869
01:29:24,489 --> 01:29:27,947
is of eternity with you.

870
01:29:30,462 --> 01:29:35,126
I offer you this rose,
Princess--

871
01:29:37,936 --> 01:29:39,870
my heart,

872
01:29:40,939 --> 01:29:42,873
my soul,

873
01:29:43,942 --> 01:29:46,001
my love.

874
01:29:46,077 --> 01:29:48,238
Love?

875
01:29:56,822 --> 01:29:59,757
[ Grunting ]

876
01:30:03,829 --> 01:30:07,390
<i>[ Lord of Darkness ]
Once l was content
with solitude...</i>

877
01:30:07,466 --> 01:30:10,060
<i>[ Gasps ]
until that moment...</i>

878
01:30:10,135 --> 01:30:13,901
<i>l felt your vivid presence.</i>

879
01:30:15,207 --> 01:30:17,175
<i>[ Gump ]
A little to the right.</i>

880
01:30:17,242 --> 01:30:20,109
<i>Left. Good!</i>

881
01:30:21,213 --> 01:30:26,708
It grows late. Sit.

882
01:30:26,785 --> 01:30:29,754
I value your thoughts.

883
01:30:29,821 --> 01:30:32,483
<i>Share them with me.</i>

884
01:31:12,797 --> 01:31:14,731
<i>Sit?
Yes.</i>

885
01:31:14,799 --> 01:31:17,632
- Nothing more than that?
- And talk with me.

886
01:31:28,246 --> 01:31:31,943
I think I'll stand,
if you don't mind.

887
01:31:32,017 --> 01:31:37,045
[ Yelling ]
Damn you!

888
01:31:37,122 --> 01:31:40,319
<i>No! Never! Never!</i>

889
01:31:43,128 --> 01:31:45,562
[ Growling ]

890
01:31:48,867 --> 01:31:50,801
[ Laughing ]

891
01:31:50,869 --> 01:31:52,632
[ Growling Continues ]

892
01:31:52,704 --> 01:31:55,298
[ Neighing ]

893
01:32:00,612 --> 01:32:03,342
<i>l hear a throat
begging to be cut.</i>

894
01:32:03,415 --> 01:32:06,384
- [ Growls ]
- [ Neighing Continues ]

895
01:32:10,789 --> 01:32:14,156
<i>Are you so... anxious...</i>

896
01:32:14,225 --> 01:32:16,216
to see blood flow?

897
01:32:16,294 --> 01:32:20,492
As you are to drink it.
Grant your bride one wish
on this night.

898
01:32:20,565 --> 01:32:22,499
You have but to ask.

899
01:32:22,567 --> 01:32:24,865
I will stay here with you
as you wish.

900
01:32:27,505 --> 01:32:29,735
- But on one condition.
- Anything.

901
01:32:31,943 --> 01:32:35,674
<i>l want to kill the Unicorn.</i>

902
01:32:40,619 --> 01:32:43,816
[ Laughing ]

903
01:32:43,888 --> 01:32:48,825
[ Roars, Laughs ]

904
01:32:55,033 --> 01:32:57,194
<i>I can't let that happen.</i>

905
01:33:06,277 --> 01:33:09,212
In the beginning...

906
01:33:09,280 --> 01:33:11,942
there was nothing--

907
01:33:14,152 --> 01:33:18,452
a void of darkness,

908
01:33:18,523 --> 01:33:22,789
<i>a cold eternity
of silence.</i>

909
01:33:24,029 --> 01:33:28,625
Jack, your greatest challenge
is still to come.

910
01:33:28,700 --> 01:33:31,498
And we have not much time.

911
01:33:31,569 --> 01:33:34,003
[ Humming ]

912
01:33:40,378 --> 01:33:44,405
When the perfect void
was corrupted...

913
01:33:44,482 --> 01:33:46,416
<i>by light,</i>

914
01:33:46,484 --> 01:33:49,647
a great wailing was heard,

915
01:33:51,322 --> 01:33:54,416
and all the brethren fled
in terror.

916
01:33:54,492 --> 01:33:57,222
Gump!

917
01:33:57,295 --> 01:33:59,525
Oona, fly up like the wind.

918
01:33:59,597 --> 01:34:01,531
It's time.

919
01:34:08,106 --> 01:34:09,869
Jack!

920
01:34:44,876 --> 01:34:46,036
<i>[ Unicorn Neighing ]</i>

921
01:34:48,880 --> 01:34:50,814
[ Neighing Continues ]

922
01:35:05,163 --> 01:35:07,097
[ Hisses ]

923
01:35:14,639 --> 01:35:16,573
<i>Lily.
[ Gump ]
Jack.</i>

924
01:35:16,641 --> 01:35:19,838
Judge her with your heart,

925
01:35:19,911 --> 01:35:22,004
<i>not your eyes.</i>

926
01:35:23,581 --> 01:35:25,515
Hear me,

927
01:35:25,583 --> 01:35:28,518
ye powers of the night!

928
01:35:28,586 --> 01:35:32,386
<i>We offer this sacrifice,</i>

929
01:35:32,457 --> 01:35:35,119
in honor of you,

930
01:35:36,194 --> 01:35:40,187
sanctified with blood...

931
01:35:40,265 --> 01:35:42,392
<i>[ Neighing Continues ]</i>

932
01:35:42,467 --> 01:35:45,231
and with fire!

933
01:35:56,281 --> 01:35:59,250
<i>l pray you, Father,</i>

934
01:35:59,317 --> 01:36:01,979
accept my sacrifice.

935
01:36:02,053 --> 01:36:07,958
<i>Let light
be forever extinguished.</i>

936
01:36:08,993 --> 01:36:13,396
<i>Let the age of darkness begin!</i>

937
01:36:13,464 --> 01:36:15,955
Come, Lady.

938
01:36:16,034 --> 01:36:20,801
The birth of a new world
awaits your stroke.

939
01:36:23,074 --> 01:36:26,601
Let my offering be made
of flesh and blood.

940
01:36:28,012 --> 01:36:31,778
She means to do it, Jack.
She's one of them.

941
01:36:31,850 --> 01:36:34,284
I am sister to the Fates.

942
01:36:34,352 --> 01:36:37,412
Kill her. Forget her.

943
01:36:37,488 --> 01:36:40,787
Think about the Unicorn.

944
01:36:48,266 --> 01:36:51,292
- Do it!
- Lily.

945
01:36:51,369 --> 01:36:55,829
- I'll do it.
- No! No.

946
01:37:00,211 --> 01:37:02,907
- I trust you, Lily.
- [ Neighing Continues ]

947
01:37:02,981 --> 01:37:05,313
I'll always trust you.

948
01:37:08,586 --> 01:37:10,747
<i>Run!</i>

949
01:37:10,822 --> 01:37:13,882
Run! You're free!

950
01:37:15,493 --> 01:37:17,552
Darkness!

951
01:37:22,233 --> 01:37:24,861
[ Grunts ]

952
01:37:25,603 --> 01:37:27,264
[ Screaming ]

953
01:37:27,338 --> 01:37:28,532
[ Growling ]

954
01:37:39,083 --> 01:37:41,017
<i>[ Arrow Whistles ]</i>

955
01:37:45,857 --> 01:37:49,623
<i>[ Jack Grunting ]
What have we here?</i>

956
01:37:49,694 --> 01:37:52,128
A little boy.

957
01:38:12,116 --> 01:38:13,947
[ Grunting Continues ]

958
01:38:18,723 --> 01:38:21,214
Screwball!
Screwball, wake up!

959
01:38:32,337 --> 01:38:34,237
[ Grunting Continues ]

960
01:38:36,174 --> 01:38:38,005
Wake up, Screwball!
Wake up!
[ Snoring ]

961
01:38:39,077 --> 01:38:43,241
It's always a pleasure
to take a brave man's life.

962
01:38:43,314 --> 01:38:45,509
[ Yelling ]

963
01:38:47,752 --> 01:38:49,117
Wake up!

964
01:39:12,677 --> 01:39:14,838
[ Laughing ]

965
01:39:17,048 --> 01:39:21,610
<i>[ Jack Screaming ]
Don't you know me, boy?</i>

966
01:39:25,590 --> 01:39:27,990
[ Laughing Continues ]

967
01:39:38,703 --> 01:39:40,796
<i>[ Grunts ]</i>

968
01:39:41,906 --> 01:39:44,170
Quickly!
What time is it?

969
01:39:44,742 --> 01:39:48,234
Every wolf suffers fleas.

970
01:39:48,312 --> 01:39:51,145
'Tis easy enough to scratch.

971
01:40:05,630 --> 01:40:08,861
Give it to me, boy!

972
01:40:11,235 --> 01:40:14,864
[ Groaning ]

973
01:40:16,507 --> 01:40:21,706
<i>[ Screaming ]</i>

974
01:40:30,221 --> 01:40:32,655
Father!

975
01:40:32,723 --> 01:40:35,783
Protect me!

976
01:40:46,571 --> 01:40:49,836
<i>You think you have won!</i>

977
01:40:51,275 --> 01:40:54,403
What is light...

978
01:40:54,479 --> 01:40:56,413
without dark?

979
01:40:57,949 --> 01:41:00,110
<i>What are you...</i>

980
01:41:00,184 --> 01:41:03,449
<i>without me?</i>

981
01:41:03,521 --> 01:41:06,581
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>

982
01:41:06,657 --> 01:41:10,252
I am a part of you all.

983
01:41:10,328 --> 01:41:15,027
<i>You can never defeat me.</i>

984
01:41:15,099 --> 01:41:17,465
<i>We are brothers...</i>

985
01:41:17,535 --> 01:41:19,264
eternal!

986
01:41:19,337 --> 01:41:22,101
Do it, Jack! Kill him!

987
01:41:22,173 --> 01:41:24,437
Kill him!

988
01:41:25,543 --> 01:41:28,478
[ Yelling ]

989
01:42:07,084 --> 01:42:09,712
<i>[ Gump ]
She's under a spell.</i>

990
01:42:09,787 --> 01:42:12,278
A powerful spell.

991
01:42:13,491 --> 01:42:15,482
Do something.

992
01:42:17,695 --> 01:42:20,323
Look what we've been through.

993
01:42:21,766 --> 01:42:24,428
Look who you are.

994
01:42:24,502 --> 01:42:26,697
Have faith in yourself.

995
01:42:26,771 --> 01:42:30,468
<i>lt is the greatest lesson
you have learned.</i>

996
01:42:30,541 --> 01:42:32,839
Only you
can answer this riddle.

997
01:42:34,912 --> 01:42:37,176
<i>[ Lily's Voice ]
l'm a princess.</i>

998
01:42:37,248 --> 01:42:40,843
It's my right to set
a challenge for my suitors.

999
01:42:40,918 --> 01:42:45,685
[ Chuckles ]
I will marry...
whoever finds this ring.

1000
01:42:48,559 --> 01:42:50,686
We too have
a promise to keep.

1001
01:42:50,761 --> 01:42:52,422
[ Snorting ]

1002
01:42:52,496 --> 01:42:55,363
Now fulfill your promise.

1003
01:42:57,034 --> 01:42:58,831
I will miss you.

1004
01:42:58,903 --> 01:43:01,929
But don't forget us.
Never.

1005
01:44:57,788 --> 01:45:00,120
I love you, Lily.

1006
01:45:01,692 --> 01:45:03,626
Come back to me.

1007
01:45:06,163 --> 01:45:08,097
Come back to me.

1008
01:45:17,274 --> 01:45:21,074
I... love you, Jack.

1009
01:45:25,149 --> 01:45:27,083
[ Sighs ]

1010
01:45:29,053 --> 01:45:31,544
[ Chuckles ]

1011
01:45:38,229 --> 01:45:40,220
I love you, Lily.

1012
01:45:41,699 --> 01:45:43,997
I had such a terrible
nightmare.

1013
01:45:44,068 --> 01:45:46,536
Did you?

1014
01:45:48,372 --> 01:45:50,306
It's over.

1015
01:45:59,517 --> 01:46:01,382
[ Laughing ]

1016
01:46:06,056 --> 01:46:08,889
Jack, was it all a dream?

1017
01:46:09,960 --> 01:46:11,689
You're safe now.

1018
01:46:15,566 --> 01:46:19,229
So many terrible things
happened.

1019
01:46:19,303 --> 01:46:21,635
I--

1020
01:46:22,706 --> 01:46:26,142
I learned something
about myself...

1021
01:46:26,210 --> 01:46:28,405
and something about you.

1022
01:46:28,479 --> 01:46:30,777
What's that?

1023
01:46:30,848 --> 01:46:33,783
You belong here.

1024
01:46:33,851 --> 01:46:36,376
You're my prince.

1025
01:46:39,190 --> 01:46:41,124
I'm only Jack.

1026
01:46:41,192 --> 01:46:43,660
My Lord Jack.

1027
01:47:24,435 --> 01:47:26,369
So you take that...

1028
01:47:26,437 --> 01:47:28,905
and you keep it,
treasure it.

1029
01:47:30,841 --> 01:47:32,775
It's part of me.

1030
01:47:36,881 --> 01:47:40,248
Can I come tomorrow?
[ Chuckles ]

1031
01:47:40,317 --> 01:47:42,251
Of course.

1032
01:47:43,487 --> 01:47:46,251
I'll be here.

1033
01:47:46,323 --> 01:47:48,723
I'll always be here
for you, Lily.

1034
01:47:55,533 --> 01:47:57,467
Will you sing for me?

1035
01:48:01,038 --> 01:48:03,438
Come down, sparrow

1036
01:48:03,507 --> 01:48:05,805
Sing me good morning

1037
01:48:05,876 --> 01:48:10,176
Rise up, sun
like the arch of the sky

1038
01:48:10,247 --> 01:48:12,306
Living river

1039
01:48:12,383 --> 01:48:14,908
Turn light to diamonds

1040
01:48:14,985 --> 01:48:18,580
When I look
in my true love's eyes

1041
01:48:55,159 --> 01:48:58,390
<i>[ Horn Blowing ]</i>

1042
01:49:00,497 --> 01:49:02,431
[ Neighs ]

1043
01:49:16,080 --> 01:49:17,479
<i>[ Neighing Continues ]</i>

1044
01:50:04,495 --> 01:50:07,430
<i>[ Choir Singing ]</i>

